content: His public personality is very colorful, having a dramatic flair. He's always seen sporting a gigantic grin, showcasing a can-do attitude even in the most desperate of situations. His enthusiasm is borderline obnoxious at times, often contagious, which leads to him being a natural leader, inspiring everyone around him. He's seen to be extremely friendly.

Even as a kid, he looked up to Heroes. This was an inspiration that didn't go away with age, in fact, it only strengthened. His father wanted him to inherit the company, but he wanted nothing more than to help others.

He realized a way to help others and not break his father's heart at the same time. He graduated with an education in Professional Heroism, at the same time, inheriting his father's company.

He now uses the company to further Humanity and his Heroics. He, along with many other ventures, invested in digging of old ruins, and research of the artifacts found within.

His company found a trident which had no wear or tear on it in an underwater ruin, and when he touched it, he immediately bonded with it. This trident granted him many strange powers, powers he uses to further his Heroics.

He is expanding the company to be worldwide, and one of his targets is WayHaven. After seeing its condition, Brook knew he HAD to help the citizens of this unfortunate city. So, he expanded his company into WayHaven, and shifted his residence to WayHaven.

It's high time for some reckoning.
Hand to Hand Combat, the Brutish kind. Polearm combat (using Trident).

He has Super strength and Super durability. He can lift 5 tons and can withstand 40000 Newtons of force on the surface, while he kicks with 30000 Newtons and punches with 25000 Newtons of force. In water, this is increased to 7 tons of weight, 45000 Newtons of force, a kick of 40000 Newtons, and a punch of 35000 Newtons. He also gains perfect vision and hearing underwater. Due to his super strength, he can vertically jump 5 Meters, and horizontally jump 12 Meters.

He holds a trident through which he channels the "twist". The trident grants him the ability to create a floating orb of water with a 3 meter diameter that traps everything within that distance of him. He can breathe perfectly inside the water as well as talk and move/swim at super speeds, increased his already enhanced durability and strength and the trident doubles as a bo staff/polearm weapon. He is impervious to aqua attacks and will be great in any water body. His speed underwater is -60mph (can accelerate to 150 mph for two turns).

The orb of water takes 2 minutes/1 turn to form, and is formed of clear water.

He cannot move the sphere from the inside, only from the outside, for which he has to swim out, he can move it at 20 mph. He can also summon creatures into the sphere, which appear beside him. The maximum combined mass of the creatures is roughly 600 pounds, so 1 Hammerhead shark which is 12 feet in length. (1000 pound hammerhead is 20 feet in length, so do the maths.)

While in water, he can "Hulk Out" to a bulky form that's 7'4" in height. In this form, his weight limit increases to 8 tons, and his durability to 50000 Newtons, however his punches remain the same strength, think of it as a swimmer pulling in their stomach and flexing by the pool to puff up their body.
He can lift heavy objects, break obstacles, jump super high, trap criminals, summon animals, and of course, traverse water bodies without any difficulty.

Once he was underneath the boat, he stabbed his trident into the underside, summoning a dolphin once the propeller stopped. The dolphin would carry the criminals back to land, as Neptune swam back with the dolphin, knocking the criminals out, and calling the police.

The setting of H&V is only inspired by the manga/anime, however, this is a non-canon server. This means that no character that exists in the BNHA world exists in here. We do however have Guilds/Agencies, Academies, Internships and other components that make up the world of BNHA. Here you can chose your path, create a character, develop the character, team up with other characters, explore the city, and battle creatures, and each other. H&V is a free-form, progressive character base server with some uses of Virtual Dice rolled by Moderators and Members

However, the action that takes place is in your imagination. In H&V you have the freedom to create anything you can imagine within the reasons of what exists on the server. What makes H&V unique is 2 reasons. The 1st is the individual Role-players. It is you that keeps the server going by making up your own story-lines. You can take on basic missions, go hunting, interact, build a world, and even train your character to become stronger. You are not limited to these examples as you can expand further. The 2nd is the Game Master. Game Masters are members of the server who carry on the role of creating a large story that impacts multiple characters. They take them on a grand adventure filled with trial, tribulation, rewards, and fun.

fields.name: Backstory
fields.value: The difference between regular role-play and events can be explained by examples. Filler Episodes or one-off adventures of Naruto dealing with a simple Mission tends to be regular Role-play. An Event, on the other hand, is when Naruto gets sent off on a Mission to lead an old man and child to a different country; later to find out he needs to battle Ninja along the way. Events are the heart of H&V. They are like a fantasy movie, or a novel while the Player Characters are the star leads in it. A Game Master makes the scene, they are the storyteller but no one knows what will happen until the Player Characters do something. Every event is different. You may explore a ruined part of the city, a dark dungeon, get lost in the woods, or have to traverse in a lava-filled cavern beneath some mountains. There could be puzzles, interaction with Non-Playable Characters, and battle creatures you normally do not meet while discovering loads of treasure.

fields.name: Best RPer
fields.value: Sin got this one, and I don't think anybody is surprised. Congratulations Dabe, you're a roleplaying genius (as if you didn't already know that)!

fields.name: Best Boy
fields.value: Our **other** resident Dave won this one! Well done! I'm giving it to you, you fuck. I don't care that you wanted me to give it to the next best.

fields.name: Best Girl
fields.value: 7 won this one! It was close between her and Lumine, I'll be honest! Honourable mention goes to Dreadknight (Liam), for **somehow** getting nominated.

fields.name: Best Hero
fields.value: Achilles won this one, probably for kicking so much villain butt! Also for playing with Stancliffe, who turned out to be a serial killer. Good job on that.

fields.name: Best Villain
fields.value: Agent Zero won this one! It was close between him, pen boi and Alexandria **'o my 100 casualties'** Argentum but he came out on top as the worst of the worst in WayHaven.

fields.name: Best Rogue
fields.value: Blank Slate won this one! You may have had a period of inactivity, but in the early part of this year you amazed us with Slate, yet again. Here's to getting blown away by Miss Mischief!

fields.name: Best Student
fields.value: Achilles won this too. He kinda did a lot while he was around, didn't he. Congratulations!

fields.name: Best Sidekick
fields.value: Lumine won this one, and I think she really deserved it! She helped to protect the city when it needed protecting, and she successfully graduated to become a fully fledged hero!

fields.name: Funniest RP
fields.value: Sin and 7 got this one, and I think most people know why. If you don't, you should definitely go check it out, it is hilarious and brilliant and beautiful.

fields.name: Saddest RP
fields.value: Ayre's death shook many of us, both due to how sudden it was, and how brutal.

fields.name: Best Fight
fields.value: This category was incredibly, incredibly close. **Exactly** third of the vote was to the alley fight between Sin and the infamous Boris, one third to Doting Baron and Alexandria's epic showdown. Still, I do believe I have to give the award to what is objectively the best fight on this server - West Wind vs Wondering Swordsman. Their intense fight in the arena resulted in new friends being forged that day, and these two are still incredibly dear to everyone's hearts.

fields.name: Best Solo RP
fields.value: Check's Final RP won this one, as she mourned StarForger's passing away in her last solo. This is a really amazing read, if you haven't seen it definitely go look for it!

fields.name: Best Non-Combat RP
fields.value: Again, this roleplay brought a major chapter of the server to a close, with Red Flare disbanding Sol Invictus, at that point the only major active hero guild to have ever existed. It expertly summarised its highs and lows, as well as each of its members, both old and current.

fields.name: Best Death
fields.value: Bandito. Duh. We actually had a funeral for him, ***UNLIKE SOMEONE ELSE***  >Glares at Su<

fields.name: Smartest RP
fields.value: This was actually a tie between VIleblood and Tao killing StarForger, and Arbiter blackfacing Dreadknight and somehow fooling an entire prison. Good job, all of you, for two very enjoyable roleplays to read!

fields.name: Best Character Development
fields.value: Red Flare won this one, although a special mention must go to Sin, who came remarkably close. Still, Red Flare's character development really was amazing, as we saw him grow and develop, always being stuck under Orion's shadow until he finally broke out of it (in a big, bad way).

fields.name: Best GM event
fields.value: The Deadwater Breakout event was really great, and won most of the votes here! We're glad you liked it so much!

fields.name: Best OC
fields.value: Sin won this one, and for good reason! Congratulations!

fields.name: Edgiest OC
fields.value: Slicer got the edgiest OC award. That's probably ironic or something. Anyway, you deserved it, you edgelord!

fields.name: Most OP quirk
fields.value: Orion won this one. He got a speeding fine going to save StarForger, and is in court contesting that - this is why he cannot be here to receive this award.

fields.name: Best Backstory
fields.value: Sin won this one too! While his backstory on the wiki is amazing enough, more and more history has been coming out in his roleplays, filling in the gaps and really fleshing Sin out as a character. Amazing job, man.

fields.name: Most Inspiring OC
fields.value: Doting Baron won this one, for being a badass.

fields.name: Most Creative Quirk
fields.value: Upchuck's gross saliva quirk won this one by a pretty huge margin. I'm not surprised, I doubt anyone else would've thought of a quirk like that!

fields.name: Most Interesting OC Concept
fields.value: Kraken won this one, and I agree with it - it was a really cool OC, and I had fun reading about the stuff he did.

fields.name: Best OC Personality
fields.value: Another three way tie. Smh. Glowstick, Red Flare **and** Sin all got a third of the votes. ~~Therefore, West Wind wins!~~ So, I rolled a dice and Glowstick won. Congratulations!

fields.name: Scariest OC
fields.value: Yeah, I'm not exactly surprised that Dreadknight won this. She's a terrifying OC, and she has shaped and reshaped this server in so many ways with her actions.

fields.name: Most Reckless OC
fields.value: Despite Agent Zero doing so many villainous acts, he sure wasn't careful. Really, it's a miracle he survived this long. The heroes need to get off their asses! Agent Zero won this one!

fields.name: Most Nerfed
fields.value: Yeah, Blood Sin won this one. ***I wonder why.***

fields.name: Best Memes for OC
